     shell command line you use to start xboard,  or  by  setting
     them  as  X  resources  (typically in your .Xdefaults file).
     Many of the options cannot be changed while xboard  is  run-
     ning;  others  set  the  initial  state of items that can be
     changed with the Options menu.

     Most of the options have both a long name and a short  name.
     To  turn  a  boolean option on or off from the command line,
     either give its long name followed  by  the  value  True  or
     False (-_l_o_n_g_O_p_t_i_o_n_N_a_m_e True), or give just the short name to
     turn the option on (-_o_p_t), or the short name preceded by "x"
     to  turn  the  option  off  (-x_o_p_t).   For options that take
     strings or numbers as values, you can use the long or  short
     option names interchangeably.

     Each option corresponds to an X resource with the same name,
     so  if you like, you can set options in your ._X_d_e_f_a_u_l_t_s file
     or in a file named  XBoard  in  your  home  directory.   For
     options  that  have two names, the longer one is the name of
     the corresponding X resource; the short name is  not  recog-
     nized.  To turn a boolean option on or off as an X resource,
     give its long name followed  by  the  value  True  or  False
     (XBoard*_l_o_n_g_O_p_t_i_o_n_N_a_m_e:  True).

